.TH LINX 1 "2026-07-19" "LinX" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
linx \- forensic correlation engine for LinSpec and K-Scanner
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B linx
[\fI--linspec FILE\fR]
[\fI--kscanner FILE\fR]
[\fI--json\fR]
[\fI--output-dir DIR\fR]
[\fI--help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
LinX cross-references LinSpec kernel hardening audit reports
with K-Scanner memory analysis results. It applies correlation rules
to identify dangerous combinations of misconfigurations and active
memory threats, producing severity-classified findings.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \--linspec FILE
Path to LinSpec report.json.
.TP
.B \--kscanner FILE
Path to K-Scanner results JSON.
.TP
.B \--json
Export findings in JSON format.
.TP
.B \--output-dir DIR
Output directory for reports (default: reports/).
.TP
.B \--help
Display this help message and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B 0
on success, 1 on error.
.SH AUTHOR
Jefferson Cesar Antunes
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR linspec (1),
.BR kscanner (1)
